352. Ipsum audite] Cf. Matt. 17. 5. Luke 9. 35, 2 Pet. 1. 17.

355. solarium] This term is com- monly used in English of an upper chamber, as towards the sun3 but- it sometimes denotes a room cut off from the great hall and giving privacy. The change in H was perhaps made by Erasmus because the classical and Vulgate (Off.) usage of the word is different, for a flat house-top or bal- cony; which would be inappropriate here.

362. immensa pecunia] Cf. Ep. 260. 20-30. ,
